<h2>2. Breathing Better</h2>

<p>Something as simple as consciously breathing has been shown to help people feel better. Deep breathing can make you feel better (it activates the parasympathetic system)
</p>

<p>It can help to count while you’re breathing. I like to breathe in for 4, and out for 4. Focusing on the count and how your breath feels in your body can help ground you in the moment. Some of you might already have noticed that this is form of mindfulness or meditation, which has been proven to help some people create resilience and a calm focus under pressure.
</p>

<p>There are many resources out there saying how many counts are good, but in my opinion the best is what works for you.
</p>

<p>So take a deep breathe in………. and out……….
</p>

