<h2>3. Find your Castle on A Cloud</h2>

<p>When I was a child, and feeling really rotten, I’d like to think of my version of a Castle on Cloud, like the one from Les Miserables (yes, I was (…*cough cough*…) am ridiculously posh). In other words, I found a “Happy Place” and put my thoughts, and in effect, myself, in it.
</p>

<p>Creating a “Happy Place” or a place in your imagination that feels safe, warm and comforting can help us by ….
</p>

<p>However, think of it as a vacation or holiday rather than a full-time residence. When you’re feeling better, it can be healthy to look at the bad things, and process them. Let it Out and, as Elsa says, “Let It Go”.
</p>

