<h2>4. You are part of something Bigger Than Yourself</h2>

<p>When you’re going through a difficult time, it can help to focus on something outside of ourselves. This can take us away from the bad thing we’re feeling in the here and now and focus our thoughts on something more bright and positive.
</p>

<p>For some people this is their religion, the idea of their god/s and what it all means to them. For other people it’s…. </p>
    
<p>For me, ‘cos I’m a bit of a hippy, I used to focus on trees, and how we’re all connected. We live by taking in plants (or animals that eat plants if you’re that way inclined), we take in water from the seas and clouds, and one day we’ll all go back to it. 

<p>The beautiful things that made us, and that we enjoyed seeing and being in and of, we will become. We’ll be in the clouds and in the water, and we’ll be in the trees. If you’re interested in this focus I’ve got a blog <a href="/blogs/You-are-made-of-stardust">here</a> that goes into it.
</p>

